{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDM0MjA3ODIy", "number": 1653, "title": "[Exam] Enhancement/exam/exercise layout", "bodyText": "Checklist\n\n I tested all changes and all related features with different users (student, tutor, instructor, admin) on the test server https://artemistest.ase.in.tum.de.\n Client: I added multiple screenshots/screencasts of my UI changes\n\nMotivation and Context\n\n\nSeparates the problem statement from the students input.\nCloses #1589 #1588 #1587\nDescription\n\n\nUse resizable-container.component to separate the problem statement and make it resizable/collapsable for Text, Modeling and File Upload Exercises\nUse media (max-width: 991.98px) for smaller screens\nRemoved border and header for exercise submissions\nSmall changes for team exercises and modeling exercise\n\nSteps for Testing\n\n\nLog in to Artemis\nNavigate to Course Administration\nCreate Text, Modeling, FileUpload Exercises and set start date to now and due date in a few minutes\nParticipate in Exercises and check if the Problem Statement is resizable/collapsable\n4.1 Check if for smaller screens the Problem Statement aligns above the students input and is not resizable/collapsable\nAfter Due Date see your Submission and check if Problem Statement is resizable/collapsable\n5.1 Check if for smaller screens the Problem Statement aligns above the students input and is not resizable/collapsable\nCheck also for team exercises\n\nNote: resizable-container.component is also used in text-submission-assessment\n7. Check if assessment instructions align above students submission for smaller screens\nScreenshots\n\n\nFile Upload:\n\nModeling:\n\nText:\n\nSmaller devices:\n\n\n\nTeam exercises:\n\n\nTeam exercises on smaller devices:", "createdAt": "2020-06-14T21:55:41Z", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1653", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "6949199a3fb2e7e709453b9ae7037bb76d21ba66"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-06-23T